de.uni_potsdam.hpi.bpt.bp2014.database

Class DbActivityInstance

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uni_potsdam.hpi.bpt.bp2014.database.DbObject
      • de.uni_potsdam.hpi.bpt.bp2014.database.DbActivityInstance

  • public class DbActivityInstance
extends DbObject
    Represents the activity instance of the database. Methods are mostly used by the HistoryService so you can get all terminated activities or start new ones.

      • setState

        public void setState(int id,
            java.lang.String state)
        This method sets the activity to a desirable state and saves a log entry into the database.
        Parameters:
        id - This is the database ID of an activity instance which is found in the database.
        state - This is the state in which an activity should be after executing setState.

      • createNewActivityInstance

        public int createNewActivityInstance(int controlNodeInstance_id,
                            java.lang.String ActivityType,
                            java.lang.String ActivityState)
        This method creates and saves a new activity instance to the database into the context of a controlNode instance and saves a log entry into the database.
        Parameters:
        controlNodeInstance_id - This is the ID of a controlNode instance which is found in the database.
        ActivityType - This is the type of an activity.
        ActivityState - This is the state of an activity.
        Returns:
        an Integer which is -1 if something went wrong else it is the database ID of the newly created activity instance.
